Field Descriptions: For Reversals "Code indicating the type of service the provider
rendered.  This code may entitle the provider to incentive fees.  Valid
values are:
00 = Not specified
01 = Patient consultation
02 = Home delivery
03 = Emergency
04 = 24 hour service
05 = Patient consultation regarding generic product selection"
The first drug conflict code submitted on the claim.  This code
identifies the type of utilization conflict that was detected during
ORDUR, or the reason for the pharmacist’s professional service.
RxTRACK captures the first three codes sent back to the p
DUR (Drug Utilization Review).  Indicates how significant the first
conflict is. This field reflects the significance that the originating
database assigned to it.
Values:
0 =  Not specified
1 =  Major
2 =  Moderate
3 =  Minor
Indicates the source of the first prescription that forms the basis for the
conflict with the current prescription. Values:
Blank = Unknown
0 = Not specified
1 = Your pharmacy
2 = Other pharmacy same chain
3 = Other pharmacy
The date of the first fill that forms the basis for the conflict with the
current prescription.
The quantity of the first fill that forms the basis for the conflict with the
current prescription.
The identifying source of the data constructing the message. Refer to
DUR 1 Database Ind.
A comparison of the current prescription’s prescriber and the
prescriber of the previously filled conflicting prescription. Values:
0 = Not applicable
1 = Same prescriber
2 = Other prescriber
Free text message sent with the first conflict code.
The second drug conflict code submitted on the claim.
Indicates how significant the second conflict is.
Indicates the source of the second prescription that forms the basis for
the conflict with the current prescription.
The date of the second fill that forms the basis for the conflict with the
current prescription.
The quantity of the second fill that forms the basis for the conflict with
the current prescription.
The identifying source of the data constructing the message. Refer to
Database Indicator 1.
A comparison of the current prescription’s prescriber and the
prescriber of the second filled conflicting prescription.
Free text message sent with the second conflict code.
The third drug conflict code submitted on the claim.
Indicates how significant the third conflict is.
Indicates the source of the third prescription that forms the basis for
the conflict with the current prescription.
The date of the third fill that forms the basis for the conflict with the
current prescription.
